    "en": {
      "title": "Another 110 to South Korea today",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Another 110 Sri Lankans who received contracts for Korean jobs are scheduled to leave for South Korea today (12th). This group is the 724th group to leave for South Korea.",
        "During the last season's discussions between the representatives of the Sri Lankan government and the representatives of the South Korean government, attention was paid to the sending of 5800 Sri Lankans for Korean jobs in 6 months. As a result, work is being done to quickly sign employment contracts and send Sri Lankans to South Korea.",
        "According to the diplomatic agreement signed between Sri Lanka and South Korea, South Korea is bringing in people for Korean jobs, and after receiving the agreements related to the Sri Lanka Foreign Employment Bureau, the work of referring the job seekers is being carried out promptly.",
        "Although there was some delay in recruitment and recruitment for foreign jobs during the Covid epidemic, the recruitment of workers for Korean jobs is growing due to the Bureau's continued cooperation with the Korean government.",
        "Meanwhile, the 725th group of 39 people leaving for Korean work is scheduled to leave for Korea tomorrow (13). Since January 2022, 3219 Sri Lankans have left for work in South Korea."
      ],
